<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. luofuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in subsect. 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSection" subSection="Virescentinae">Russula Virescentinae</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetically, our new species 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. luofuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="luofuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. luofuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clustered with 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. albidogrisea" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="albidogrisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. albidogrisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 89% bootstrap support and 1.00 posterior probabilities, which is also from Guangdong Province of China. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. albidogrisea" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="albidogrisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. albidogrisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. luofuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="luofuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. luofuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a white to grayish pileus with acute, even to slightly undulate margin, often smaller basidiospores [(5.1-)5.3-5.6-6.0(-6.4) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(4.6-)4.8-5.1-5.3(-5.6) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
], longer hymenial gloeocystidia on lamellae sides (35-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and hymenial gloeocystidia on lamellae edges (37-46 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9-12 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v38.iss3.2017.353" author="Das, K" journalOrPublisher="Cryptogamie Mycologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="353 - 406" refId="B13" refString="Das, K, Ghosh, A, Chakraborty, D, Li, JW, Qiu, LH, Baghela, A, Halama, M, Hembrom, ME, Mehmood, T, Parihar, A, Pencakowski, B, Bielecka, M, Reczynska, K, Sasiela, D, Singh, U, Song, Y, Świerkosz, K, Szczesniak, K, Uniyal, P, Zhang, JB, Buyck, B, 2017. Fungal Biodiversity Profiles 31-40. Cryptogamie Mycologie 38 (3): 353 - 406, DOI: https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v38.iss3.2017.353" title="Fungal Biodiversity Profiles 31 - 40." url="https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v38.iss3.2017.353" volume="38" year="2017">Das et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Given cracking surface, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. viridirubrolimbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="viridirubrolimbata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. viridirubrolimbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. parvovirescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="parvovirescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. parvovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. crustosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="crustosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. crustosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Peck of subsect. 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSection" subSection="Virescentinae">Russula Virescentinae</taxonomicName>
resemble 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. luofuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="luofuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. luofuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. viridirubrolimbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="viridirubrolimbata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. viridirubrolimbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from China, can be distinguished by a light yellowish olive to yellowish olive pileus center with a pinkish red to light jasper red margin and absence of hymenial gloeocystidia on lamellae edges (
<bibRefCitation author="Ying, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Acta Mycologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="34 - 37" refId="B37" refString="Ying, JZ, 1983. A study on Russula viridi-rubrolimata sp. nov. and its related species of subsection Virescentinas. Acta Mycologica Sinica 2 (1): 34 - 37" title="A study on Russula viridi-rubrolimata sp. nov. and its related species of subsection Virescentinas." volume="2" year="1983">Ying 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Deng, CY" journalOrPublisher="Mycosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 23" refId="B15" refString="Deng, CY, Shi, LY, Wang, J, Xiang, Z, Li, SM, Li, GJ, Yang, H, 2020. Species diversity of Russula virescens complex &quot;qingtoujun&quot; in southern China. Mycosystema 39: 1 - 23" title="Species diversity of Russula virescens complex &quot; qingtoujun &quot; in southern China." volume="39" year="2020">Deng et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The American species 
<taxonomicName genus="R." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="R. parvovirescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="parvovirescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">R. parvovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a greenish brown to metallic bluish green pileus with green patches (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/15572536.2006.11832664" author="Buyck, B" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="612 - 615" refId="B7" refString="Buyck, B, Mitchell, D, Parrent, J, 2006. Russula parvovirescens sp. nov., a common but ignored species in the eastern United States. Mycologia 98: 612 - 615, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/15572536.2006.11832664" title="Russula parvovirescens sp. nov., a common but ignored species in the eastern United States." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/15572536.2006.11832664" volume="98" year="2006">Buyck et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula virescens" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Russula virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(originally reported from Europe) is distinct in its green to yellowish green pileus (
<bibRefCitation author="Sarnari, M" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B26" refString="Sarnari, M, 1998. Monografia illustrate de genere Russula in Europa. Tomo Secondo. AMB, Centro Studi Micologici, Trento." title="Monografia illustrate de genere Russula in Europa. Tomo Secondo. AMB, Centro Studi Micologici, Trento." year="1998">Sarnari 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula albidogrisea" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albidogrisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Russula albidogrisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally reported from North America, has a brownish-yellow, greenish or subolivaceous pileus with small spot-like areolae or pseudo-verrucae, shorter basidia [(29-)30-32-33.5(-35) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(7.5-)8-9.5-10.5(-11) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
] and absence of hymenial gloeocystidia on the lamellar edges (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v39.iss1.2018.3" author="Adamcik, S" journalOrPublisher="Cryptogamie Mycologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="3 - 108" refId="B1" refString="Adamcik, S, Jancovicova, S, Buyck, B, 2018. The Russulas described by Charles Horton Peck. Cryptogamie Mycologie 39 (1): 3 - 108, DOI: https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v39.iss1.2018.3" title="The Russulas described by Charles Horton Peck." url="https://doi.org/10.7872/crym/v39.iss1.2018.3" volume="39" year="2018">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Adamčík">Adamcik</normalizedToken>
et al. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
